  "body": "I'm doing `go test` for `core/blockchain_test.go`, when I changed [TestChainConfig](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/params/config.go#L251) in `prarams/config.go`, more specific speak, I changed `ByzantiumBlock` from `big.NewInt(0)` to `big.NewInt(1)`, and other fields like `ConstantinopleBlock ` and `PetersburgBlock `. \r\nSome test cases in `blockchain_test.go` (e.g: `TestFastVsFullChains`) fails with error:\r\n```\r\nfailed to process block 0: invalid merkle root (remote: 7d390f1b910e5da714bb029167ca9a67a0495f6e6d3624aa5806945e8945cdc4 local: 2d1d708f4aa049f491757eea5031b8c1eefa93dd5c9bcc60741de767f8d4c4f2)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhy use `0` as height for `ByzantiumBlock`, `ConstantinopleBlock` and other fork height in Test? Why couldn't use a none-zero value?\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth 1.9.22`\r\nOS & Version: OSX\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n1. change `TestChainConfig`\r\n```\r\nTestChainConfig = &ChainConfig{big.NewInt(1), big.NewInt(0), nil, false, big.NewInt(0), common.Hash{}, big.NewInt(0), big.NewInt(0), big.NewInt(1), big.NewInt(0), big.NewInt(0), big.NewInt(30), nil, nil, nil, new(EthashConfig), nil}\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. go test it\r\n```\r\ngo test -timeout 30s github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/core -run ^TestFastVsFullChains$ -v\r\n```\r\n",
